Dar, the founding member of the Sidara group, is an international multidisciplinary consulting organization specializing in engineering, architecture, planning, environment, project management, facilities management, and economics. Sidara operates in 60 countries with 20,500 professionals, Dar connects people, places, and communities through innovative solutions to the world's most complex challenges. We deliver projects from inception through completion, embracing challenges to empower communities worldwide. Learn more at www.dar.com.




Overview

Urban Data Scientist will work within the dedicated multi-disciplinary team, contributing to projects forward through data-driven insights developed in close collaboration with architects, planners, designers, and economists, the successful candidate will leverage big data to inform decisions on projects varying in scale, from local enhancements to comprehensive urban redevelopment. This role demands a blend of technical proficiency and a deep understanding of urban systems to uncover patterns and trends that will shape sustainable and vibrant urban spaces.




Key Responsibilities

Understanding of the design/masterplan processes and revise a research methodology appropriate to the project scope and timescale;
Identifying and automating data collection processes;
Pre-process structured and unstructured data to facilitate analysis;
Utilising statistical and machine learning models to identify trends and inform project development from the outset;
Developing project-specific urban analytics methodologies to integrate into planning and design processes;
The ability to coherently present findings both verbally and visually to a wide range of professionals, clients and consultants with varying degrees of data literacy.




Skills and Qualifications

Postgraduate diploma in Urban Studies or related urban planning/design context, with an Undergraduate in a scientific field such as Geography, Statistics;
Minimum 2-5 years’ work experience in urban design / master planning practice;
Programming experience, code writing and prototyping purposes in languages such as Python, Java, C++;
Working proficiency in GIS software (ArcGIS, QGIS), experience in manipulation and analysis of both real-time and static data sets, with a focus on geospatial and urban data analysis;
Excellent presentation skills;
Experience in working on projects in the MENA Region is advantageous.




